doc.ContractDescription: THE DISKS AROUND PRE-MAIN-SEQUENCE STARS PROVIDE THE RESERVOIRS OF RAW MATERIAL AND INITIAL CONDITIONS FOR THE FORMATION OF PLANETARY SYSTEMS. THESE GAS-RICH PROTOPLANETARY DISKS LINK PROTOSTARS AND PLANETS BOTH PHYSICALLY AND CHEMICALLY. WHILE THE THEORY AND MODELING OF PROTOPLANETARY DISKS IS CURRENTLY THE SUBJECT OF INTENSE EFFORT, CONSTRAINTS FROM SYSTEMATIC OBSERVATIONAL STUDIES OF GAS TRACERS REMAIN SCARCE. THERE IS LITTLE OR NO OBSERVATIONAL UNDERPINNING FOR MANY IMPORTANT ASPECTS, SUCH AS THE CONSEQUENCES OF IRRADIATION BY STARS OF DIFFERENT SPECTRAL TYPES, THE DEEPER ULTRAVIOLET PENETRATION ENABLED BY DUST COAGULATION AND SETTLING, AND THE EFFECTS OF ENERGETIC RADIATION GENERATED BY ACCRETION. WE PROPOSE A THREE PART PROGRAM TO STUDY THE MAIN PHYSICAL DRIVERS OF CHEMICAL EVOLUTION IN DISKS AS FOLLOWS: (1) WE WILL USE MILLIMETER INTERFEROMETRY TO MAKE THE FIRST RESOLVED SURVEY OF MOLECULAR TRACERS IN A SAMPLE OF STAR+DISK SYSTEMS WITH A RANGE OF PROPERTIES. THIS SURVEY, WHICH WE HAVE JUST STARTED WITH THE SUB MILLIMETER ARRAY, TARGETS IONIZATION IN THE DIFFERENT PARTS OF DISKS (HCO+, N2H+, H2D+), SIGNPOSTS OF PHOTON-DOMINATED CHEMISTRY (HCN, CN), DEUTERATION (DCO+, DCN, H2D+), AND ICE-EVAPORATION (H2CO, CH3OH); (2) WE WILL USE DETAILED RADIATIVE TRANSFER CALCULATIONS TO RETRIEVE PARAMETRIC RADIAL (AND SOMETIMES VERTICAL) CHEMICAL ABUNDANCE INFORMATION BY FITTING THE OBSERVED LINE EMISSION IN THE CONTEXT OF DISK STRUCTURE MODELS DERIVED TO MATCH FULL SPECTRAL ENERGY DISTRIBUTIONS AND SPATIALLY RESOLVED MILLIMETER DUST EMISSION; (3) WE WILL USE STATE-OF-THE-ART CHEMICAL NETWORK MODELS TO DETERMINE HOW THE TARGETED SPECIES BEHAVE FOR THE OBSERVED RANGE OF STAR+DISK SYSTEMS, AND TO ELUCIDATE A DEEPER UNDERSTANDING OF ANY OBSERVED TRENDS. WE ALSO AIM TO DEVELOP DETAILED, SOURCE-SPECIFIC MODELS TO COMPARE WITH OBSERVATIONS. AS THE PROPOSED WORK WILL ADVANCE OUR KNOWLEDGE OF THE PHYSICAL CONDITIONS AND CHEMICAL PROCESSES IN PLANET-FORMING DISKS, THE PROGRAM IS DIRECTLY RELEVANT TO THE GOALS OF THE ORIGINS OF SOLAR SYSTEMS PROGRAM AND TO THE NASA STRATEGIC PLAN. IN ADDITION, THE SPATIALLY AND SPECTRALLY RESOLVED MILLIMETER OBSERVATIONS OF GAS TRACERS AND DUST IN DISKS WILL PROVIDE AN ESSENTIAL COMPLEMENT TO THE WEALTH OF SHORTER WAVELENGTH DATA COMING FROM MAJOR NASA MISSIONS, INCLUDING HUBBLE, SPITZER, HERSCHEL AND SOFIA. THIS PROGRAM IS A STEPPING STONE TOWARD THE GOAL OF REALIZING THE FULL POTENTIAL OF TRACE MOLECULAR SPECIES OTHER THAN CO AS PRIMARY TOOLS TO PROBE THE STRUCTURE OF, AND PROCESSES WITHIN, PROTOPLANETARY DISKS.

MASSACHUSETTS SUMMER OF INNOVATION (MA SOL) PROJECT IMPLEMENTATION&MANAGEMENT: MASSACHUSETTS SPACE GRANT (MASGC) HAS REVIEWED NUMEROUS STEM PROGRAMS SPANNING THE STATE AND HAS SELECTED 10 INNOVATIVE AND PROVEN STEM EDUCATION PROGRAMS FOR MIDDLE SCHOOL STUDENTS AND TEACHERS, BRINGING TOGETHER 14 EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTIONS AND INDUSTRIES IN THE STATE: 1. ZERO-ROBOTICS - AURORA FLIGHT SYSTEMS, MIT SPACE SYSTEMS LABORATORY, MA AFTERSCHOOL PARTNERSHIP. 2. LIVING IN SPACE USING LEGO ROBOTICS - TUFTS, CHRISTA MCAULIFFE CHALLENGER LEARNING CENTER. 3. DYNAMIC EARTH AND SPACE - BOSTON MUSEUM OF SCIENCE. 4. USING STARLAB AS YOUR CLASSROOM - MA COLLEGE OF LIBERAL ARTS. 5. GODDARD GIRLS - UMASS MEDICAL SCHOOL. 6. STEM IN SPACE SCIENCES - WORCESTER POLYTECHNIC INSTITUTE. 7. TALENTED&GIFTED LATINO ASTRONOMY PROGRAM - UMASS BOSTON, KAVLI INSTITUTE FOR ASTROPHYSICS. 8. YOU GO GIRLS - EDGERTON CENTER. 9. SUMMER MATH - MOUNT HOLYOKE. 10. MATH&SCIENCE OF BASEBALLS - MIT OFFICE OF ENGINEERING OUTREACH PROGRAMS. THESE PROGRAMS WILL BE ADAPTED FOR THE MA SUMMER OF INNOVATION (MA SOL), AND, IMPLEMENTED, MANAGED, TRACKED AND EVALUATED BY NASA CONTENT WITH HANDS-ON ACTIVITIES: NASA CONTENT WILL BE EMPHASIZED IN AN THE PROGRAMS DURING THE SUMMER OF 2010. FOR EXAMPLE, THE ZERO-ROBOTICS PROGRAM UTILIZES THE SPHERES FLIGHT EXPERIMENT IN USE ON THE INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION, WITH DEDICATED TIME ALREADY AVAILABLE; AND THE LIVING IN SPACE PROGRAM WILL TEACH ENGINEERING FUNDAMENTALS USING LEGO TOOLKITS, UTILIZING NASA MODULES SUCH AS KIDS CAPTURE THE UNIVERSE. TARGETS: THE PROGRAMS TARGET AT-RISK STUDENTS, GIRLS, UNDERSERVED MINORITIES, AND STUDENTS WITH DISABILITIES. MA SOL WILL SPECIFICALLY INCLUDE THE PERKINS SCHOOL FOR THE BLIND AND THE LEARNING INSTITUTE FOR THE DEAF AMONG TARGETED SCHOOLS. IMPACT: GIVEN THAT 9 OF OUR 10 PROPOSED PROGRAMS INVOLVE STEM TRAINING FOR EDUCATORS, MA SOL WILL IMPACT STUDENTS NOT ONLY THROUGH DIRECT PARTICIPATION IN THE SUMMER OF 2010, BUT WILL ALSO IMPACT STUDENTS WHO ARE TAUGHT DURING THE COMING SCHOOL YEAR BY PARTICIPATING TEACHERS AND FOLLOW-UP ACTIVITIES SUCH AS LIVE STREAMING IN SCHOOL THEATERS. ACCORDING TO THE ESTIMATES TABULATED IN THE PROPOSAL DESCRIPTION, AN ESTIMATED 5,222 TEACHERS AND 27,832 STUDENTS WILL BE IMPACTED BY MA SOL. STATE GOVERNMENT SUPPORT: MA SOL HAS SPECIAL SUPPORT FROM THE LIEUTENANT GOVERNOR AND IS ALIGNED WITH THE MA DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION GOALS EVIDENCED BY THE FOLLOWING EXCERPTS FROM THE LETTER OF SUPPORT INCLUDED IN THE PROPOSAL: "WE AS A STATE ARE READY TO ASSIST YOUR CONSORTIUM AS YOU IMPLEMENT, OVERSEE, AND TRACK THE POLICY AND FUNDING GOALS AND INITIATIVES OF THE SUMMER OF INNOVATION PROGRAM." " ... THE GOALS OUTLINED IN PRESIDENT'S EDUCATE TO INNOVATE INITIATIVE AND THE CRITERIA FOR THIS GRANT ARE VERY WELL ALIGNED WITH ... THE MASSACHUSETTS RACE TO THE TOP REQUEST AND THE GOVERNOR'S EDUCATION ACTION AGENDA." EVALUATION, TRACKING, AND COORDINATION WITH THE STATE: MASGC WILL WORK CLOSELY WITH A STATE AGENCY, THE DONAHUE INSTITUTE (UMDI), DRAWING ON INSTRUMENTS, PROTOCOLS AND PROCESSES UMDI HAS USED FOR THE PAST FIVE YEARS IN COLLECTING STATEWIDE DATA FOR THE US DEPT. OF ED.-FUNDED "IMPROVING TEACHER QUALITY" AND THE STATE'S PIPELINE FUND PROGRAMS. WITH TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE FROM UMDI, EVIDENCED BY THEIR LETTER OF SUPPORT AND DETAILED IN THE PROGRAM DESCRIPTION, MASGC WILL TRACK PARTICIPANTS, ASSESS EFFECTIVENESS, ANALYZE DATA AND REPORT IN THE CONTEXT OF THE STATE'S EDUCATION FRAMEWORK AND RELEVANCE FOR THE NASA OFFICE OF EDUCATION PERFORMANCE METRICS. KICK-OFF EVENT: MASGC WILL INITIATE THE PROGRAM WITH PARTICIPANTS, NASA LEADERSHIP AND THE STATE GOVERNMENT AT THE BOSTON MUSEUM OF SCIENCE, WHERE MASGC HELPED NASA HOLD THE FUTURE FORUM.
